"Elements that seem to indicate that the vessel had several contact with the ground, the wings came into contact with trees 25 metres away from the fluid."
He also reported that the vessel was intended for 19 persons, thus meeting the necessary requirements for the transport of persons.
He also said that studies conducted in the area of impact did not report the presence of parts on the ground.
"The study reports that elsewhere there are no components of the vessel, and the impact occurred in a state of structural integrity.
"The helicopter was intended for 19 passengers, which met the corresponding requirements for the transport of passengers.
The land in this place has a gradient of seven to 30 degrees.
