The Fukushima accident doesn't change any of these factors.
That is why Germany remains alone in its decision to abandon nuclear energy.
This is not the case of Belgium, which makes its decision dependent on the need to find a source capable of replacing nuclear power, or of Switzerland, which intends to build only the most modern reactors.
